<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>1981-01-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Evidence that the genome of hepatitis A virus consists of single-stranded RNA.</TITLE><BODY>Nucleic acid was extracted from purified hepatitis A virus, radiolabeled with 125I, and shown to consist of single-stranded RNA which sediments at 35S and contains sequences of polyadenylic acid. These findings are consistent with hepatitis A virus being a member of the genus Enterovirus within the family Picornaviridae.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>